Significant Items Affecting the Results of Operations
Our net income and other financial measures as shown above for the year ended December 31, 2015 have been affected by, among other things, the following significant items:
1)
The Catlin Acquisition;
2)
The impact of significant large loss events, including the Tianjin, China port explosion;
3)
The sale of our interest in our operating affiliate, ARX;
4)
Continuing competitive factors impacting the underwriting environment;
5)
Net favorable prior year loss development; and
6)
Market movement impacts on our investment portfolio.
1)     Catlin Acquisition
On May 1, 2015, we completed the acquisition of Catlin for $4.1 billion. See Item 8, Note 3(c), "Acquisitions and Disposals - Catlin Acquisition," for further details.
2)
The impact of significant large loss events
